      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the fan giving you a brief spin before dying again could indeed suggest an electrical issue or a problem with the power supply to the motor. One common culprit in such cases is the capacitor, which helps the motor start and run smoothly. If it's failing, it might cause intermittent behavior like you're experiencing. Another possibility could be a faulty relay or a loose connection in the wiring. When inspecting, look for any signs of corrosion or damage on the wiring and connections. If you're comfortable with it, you can also check the capacitor with a multimeter to see if it's functioning properly. However, if you're unsure, it's best to consult a professional to avoid any potential hazards. Remember, when dealing with electrical components, safety first!",
